gomodel:SYNGO_523  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors detected Huntingtin in synaptosomal fractions of human brain and anti-huntingtin antisera immunoprecipitated structures containing the vesicle-associated protein synaptophysin, which suggest the presence of the protein in synaptic contacts and, more specifically, presynaptic compartments. Immunogold labeling of a synaptosome fraction from human cortex and ultrastructural labeling using a peroxidase-based reaction performed in human cortical neurons confirm the presence within the presynaptic compartment.\n\n11/5/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \"At the ultrastructural level, peroxidase reaction product in human cortical neurons was dispersed in patches within the matrix of the cytoplasm and was concentrated on and around the membranes of vesicles in cell bodies, proximal and distal dendrites (Figure 5g), ...\". Experimental description: From M&M: Human brain tissue from three normal control cases was obtained from the Brain Tissue Resource Center at McLean Hospital, Belmont, MA" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-06-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_523" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

